casebody.data:
People ex rel. Truman Hunt v. Kalamazoo Circuit Judge. Q. M. Buck for the motion. T. B. Sherwood against.

Stipulation to extend time for settling exceptions.

When the counsel for both parties have stipulated to extend time for settling exceptions, their stipulation removes the necessity of foEowing the rules, and the court has no right to disregard it. Per Curiam.

Motion for order to show cause.

Submitted and granted June 18.
